","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the tube from the magnetic rack and mix by gently inverting the tube 20 times to resuspend the bead pellet in the washing solution (probably it won't be entirely resuspendend and there will be some small\/big bead aggregates floating - if that happens, don't worry).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871892,"guid":"99CD99003D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871891,"previous_guid":"6879BAA03D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EDAF34320D2D4B7BAD8714F80640A919","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E2C21BF6FACB49EDA2C07CDB1A58C37D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin down for 1 second.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871893,"guid":"A01A73A03D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871892,"previous_guid":"99CD99003D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4E2CADDA9C004DAFA4EC140D8591ED7E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"93EFE299851444C7A104CDCC879F35F5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place the tube on a magnetic rack and wait until all beads bind at the back of the tube and the solution becomes clear.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871894,"guid":"AC2640C03D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871893,"previous_guid":"A01A73A03D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"026DD6AB042D43798EEC91CD76BC7F07","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"327B93FA901C4E078F28F5F92BD5E99C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the supernatant without disturbing the bead pellet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871895,"guid":"B7CFA2903D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871894,"previous_guid":"AC2640C03D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1CF79DAA2ED64DC0A6BB43E41F5363CB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B96BA666043E471CA982DCB2EDE58964","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat steps 20 - 24 two-three times (total possible washing = 4 times, but usually 2 washes are enough).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871896,"guid":"16BE27E03D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871895,"previous_guid":"B7CFA2903D4411EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A66480A3E0224E33998B8E472C3BBAA0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"736B284943F1458DB46CEFFD200CB40B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin down for 1 second and remove the remaining washing solution with a P10 pipette.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871897,"guid":"25FE6C103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871896,"previous_guid":"16BE27E03D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"28263A672666473F917A0A14977313A5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AB2505F8BAA6473CAE30DADD82547D3A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 50 \u00b5l EB (or Tris-HCl 10 mM pH=8.5).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871898,"guid":"5368DB403D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871897,"previous_guid":"25FE6C103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"65E769F3C85645D9A6DB35D7AE72E778","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"591C226B64B74706BF70462C5014ECD2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend the beads by gently swirling or flicking the tube. This time they must be completely resuspended. It is important that the beads are not aggregated, or the elution efficiency will be reduced. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871899,"guid":"76DB1B103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871898,"previous_guid":"5368DB403D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D27F5150C19E4940A03F681371347F84","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5AB217CD8695427CB5E259B240CD19ED","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate at 37 \u00b0C for 15 minutes and flick the tube again.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":900},{"id":871900,"guid":"7EB4D7403D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871899,"previous_guid":"76DB1B103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F5252D96A0874FCF97487E365D95C881","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E4D5671DA6FA427CA95C27D4FEE93B07","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin down for 1 second.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871901,"guid":"82D7F4103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871900,"previous_guid":"7EB4D7403D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DBD9FB77BBF448C292ADDC90BA6F2425","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2BA9C045891F4B6E97ECA1358033FF5E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place the tube on a magnetic rack and wait until all beads bind at the back of the tube and the solution becomes clear. If DNA is at high concentration, this can take a long time. You can leave it overnight at RT, and\/or add more EB (if you do so mix by flicking the tube after the addition of EB and put the tube back on the Magnetic Rack).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":1800},{"id":871902,"guid":"D2756C503D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871901,"previous_guid":"82D7F4103D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DD9E2A77D936433E964C3631E474A877","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F59732D5699F4FBAAC49EBE00A1DC227","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the eluted DNA into a new tube, with a cut tip, or using a wide-bore tip, as DNA is very concentrated and the solution very viscous.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871904,"guid":"2D6796B03D4611EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":871902,"previous_guid":"D2756C503D4511EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EC3E4E3B7E374D808C033F556E3BF9D0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Genomic DNA Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6389E77068D54872A899B82AB3E28260","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Leave the DNA at RT overnight, as the HMW DNA is very aggregated and needs to get relaxed and homogenized. The day after proceed with Nanodrop lecture, to determine the purity, and Qubit to determine concentration. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#d0021b","section_duration":5400,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871998,"guid":"3D3EFAB03D5A11EA9823B14B6D3567C6","previous_id":787022,"previous_guid":"D9F1CFB0AECE11E98F66AFC19C29E890","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EF68A6E8D1B746D9845E028CF327D5BC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Cell Lysis"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F13DFBE8EEE349FEA653E434D0F1B9F1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Grind ~100-110 mg leaf tissue in LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> with mortar and pestle. This is a crucial step as it will affect final DNA yield, purity, and integrity.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Plant leaves must be flash frozen in LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>immediately after harvesting and stored at -80 \u00b0C until DNA extraction procedure, if not immediately used. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Here a useful tutorial on how to grind plant tissue with LN<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/bionanogenomics.com\/videos\/liquid-nitrogen-grinding-tutorial\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/bionanogenomics.com\/videos\/liquid-nitrogen-grinding-tutorial\/<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> . As they say: \"Keep grinding until powder is as fine as wheat flour\"<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Tips to achieve better results: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Apply enough pressure to allow cells to break and recover as much DNA as possible. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>- Keep the powder frozen until it goes into the lysis buffer<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">, <\/span><span>by adding LN2 while grinding<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> <\/span><span>(LN2 evaporates quickly). This prevents nuclease activation and oxidation processes<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> <\/span><span>(once powder is in the lysis buffer, the nucleases will be inactivated by the SDS and EDTA, and the oxidation blocked by BME and Metabisulfite)<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":3600,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":879625,"guid":"16F263A0494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","previous_id":871904,"previous_guid":"2D6796B03D4611EA9823B14B6D3567C6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7A62EBF304194A6498EB90CEAD5866EA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Additional Purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0FBD534844294040A533CCF3C2A6B128","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">An additional purification steps can improve the A260\/A280 and A260\/A230 ratios. At this step you can pool the elution of multiple tubes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Before starting: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Incubate the Beads Solution at RT for more than 30 minutes prior to use;<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Mix the beads by vortexing for 20 seconds before use .<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat steps 15 to 33.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":879628,"guid":"BBDA4540494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","previous_id":879625,"previous_guid":"16F263A0494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"95FEE34681B749BA9F10F8D61941F5C4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"QC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"030D3F1CBC574EEEBCDE4DD88CE1FF2D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Determine the purity of the DNA at 230, 260, 280 nm with a spectrophotometer (e.g. NanoDrop 2000). Acceptable values are:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- A260\/280 = 1.8 - 2.0;<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- A260\/230 = 2.0 - 2.2.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">A260\/280 >2.0 or A260\/230 >2.2 could be indicative of a contamination by RNA. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":879629,"guid":"BBE800E0494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","previous_id":879628,"previous_guid":"BBDA4540494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"008F225215244573AF1ED2737EF0E150","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"QC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1139CF9F5D4B44EB8902500B2491D9F1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Determine the concentration of double-stranded DNA with a fluorimetric-based method (e.g. Qubit 3.0 Fluorometer BR assay). The ratio between the concentration measured with Nanodrop, over the concentration measured by Qubit should be <2. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":879631,"guid":"38118EE0494411EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","previous_id":879629,"previous_guid":"BBE800E0494011EAB53E97C6C3D2F225","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EB19E790A36A4A43B7464106B15795FC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"QC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CA0A279A36A847AFA5650513641DABF3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Evaluate DNA integrity on a TapeStation, and fragment length on PhemtoPulse (or PFGE).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":[],"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[{"id":4542,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Buffer EB","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/shop\/lab-basics\/buffers-and-reagents\/buffer-eb\/#orderinginformation","sku":"19086","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Qiagen","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/products\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":25},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":204767,"mol_weight":0,"name":"SeraMag SpeedBeads Carboxyl-Magnet-Beads hydrophob","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.fishersci.se\/shop\/products\/sera-mag-speedbeads-carboxyl-magnetic-beads-hydrophobic-3\/11819912","sku":"GE Healthcare 65152105050250","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Fisher Scientific","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.fishersci.com\/us\/en\/home.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":31},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":349246,"mol_weight":0,"name":"RNAse A (DNAse free) 100mg\/ml ","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/products\/discovery-and-translational-research\/lab-essentials\/enzymes\/rnase-a\/#orderinginformation","sku":"19101","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Qiagen","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/products\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":25},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Modified from the protocol of Baptiste Mayjonade, J\u00e9rome Gouzy, C\u00e9cile Donnadieu, Nicolas Pouilly, William Marande, Caroline Callot, Nicolas Langlade and St\u00e9phane Munos, High molecular weight gDNA extraction, Bio Techniques, Vol. 61, No. 4, October 2016, pp. 203-205. BioTechniques 61:203-205 (October 2016) doi 10.2144\/000114460<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.future-science.com\/doi\/10.2144\/000114460\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.future-science.com\/doi\/10.2144\/000114460<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The original protocol failed to extract High Molecular Weight genomic DNA from orchids samples (poor yield and low purity). Therefore modifications (mainly\/mostly BME addition during the lysis step and a Phenol:Chloroform purification step) were made to create a new version of this protocol. This new version allowed to successfully extract DNA from orchid samples. This DNA was then sequenced on a Nanopore PromethION platform and good results in term of total yield and read length were obtained. This protocol was also successfully applied to a wide range of plant species (See attached document\/excel sheet).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">ACKNOWLEDGEMENT<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sequencing of the <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Arabidopsis thaliana<\/span><span> samples listed in the attached reports was performed in collaboration with the GeT core facility, Toulouse, France (<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/get.genotoul.fr)\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">http:\/\/get.genotoul.fr)<\/span><\/a><span>,  and was supported by France G\u00e9nomique National infrastructure, funded  as part of \u201cInvestissement d\u2019avenir\u201d program managed by Agence Nationale  pour la Recherche (contract ANR-10-INBS-09). We particularly want to thank Lisa Gil and C\u00e9line Lopez-Roques for the sequencing part and Roxane Boyer for the data processing.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sampling and DNA Extraction for the <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Ophrys sphegodes <\/span><span>samples were financially supported by the University of Z\u00fcrich Research Priority Programme URPP \"Evolution in Action\" (PMS\/AR). Sequencing was performed by Daniel Frei in the Department of Molecular Diagnostics, Genomics and Bioinformatics, Agroscope W\u00e4denswil, Switzerland. We are thankful to J\u00fcrg E. Frey, Agroscope, for financial support. We are grateful to Philipp M. Schl\u00fcter and Ueli Grossniklaus for support and helpful discussion.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sequencing of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Lolium multiflorium <\/span><span>was performed in Agroscope by Daniel Frei. We thank Daniel, J\u00fcrg E. Frei, Dario Copetti and Bruno Studer, Department of Environmental Systems Science,  ETH Z\u00fcrich, for sharing the sequencing results.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sequencing of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Brassica incana <\/span><span>was performed at FGCZ Z\u00fcrich. We are thankful to L\u00e9a Frachon, Department of Systematic and Evolutionary Botany, UZH Z\u00fcrich, to share the data.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>DNA extraction of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Gorteria diffusa <\/span><span>was performed by Roman T. Kellenberger, Department of Plant Sciences, University of Cambridge. We wish to thank him for sharing his sequencing results. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1618236845}